  "text": "The acceptance of hidden illness per se is perhaps something that a manager and human resource (HR) staff can suggest is not in their province if it is not raised by an employee. However, studies show that concealment of mental illness is more common than its disclosure, as is the case for a number of other chronic illnesses [CITATION_1] . Meanwhile, the World Health Organisation (WHO 2005) points out that the costs of mental illness are too high to be ignored as it has multiple cost loadings within each affected organisation and the wider community.",
